.TH DOVAHKIIN 1 "2026-04-22" "dovahkiin 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dovahkiin \- FUS RO DAH! Random Skyrim quotes from Alduin's scroll
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dovahkiin
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dovahkiin
displays random Skyrim quotes inside an ASCII art scroll held by Alduin,
the World-Eater. Each run shows a different quote from guards, NPCs, and
legends of Skyrim.
.PP
You can also pass your own text with the \fB\-\-quote\fR option.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quote " " \fITEXT\fR
Display custom text in the scroll instead of a random Skyrim quote.
Maximum 260 characters. Text longer than this will be truncated.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version number and credits inside Alduin's scroll.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show a random Skyrim quote:
.B dovahkiin
.TP
Show custom text:
.B dovahkiin \-q \(dqFus Ro Dah!\(dq
.TP
Show version and credits:
.B dovahkiin \-v
.SH ASCII ART
The Alduin ASCII art was created by Alan Greep.
.br
Source: https://asciiart.website/art/1469
